headline: Will Federal Realty (FRT) Earnings Guidance Shape Its Long-Term Growth and Dividend Story?
summary: Federal Realty Investment Trust recently reported its third-quarter 2025 earnings, revealing year-over-year increases in sales and revenue, affirmed its regular quarterly dividends, and updated its full-year earnings guidance. Despite higher net income for the nine-month period, earnings per share for the third quarter remained largely unchanged from a year earlier, highlighting a mixed performance. headline: Federal Realty Investment Trust Reports Third Quarter 2025 Results
summary: Federal Realty Investment Trust (NYSE:FRT) today reported its results for the third quarter ended September 30, 2025. For the three months ended September 30, 2025 and 2024, net income available for common shareholders was $0.69 per diluted share and $0.70 per diluted share, respectively. Operating income for the same periods was $110.7 million and $105.8 million, respectively.
